The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 1.6
percent to 1,484.44 by 12:31 a.m.in Moscow, paring an earlier
loss of as much as 2.1 percent. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
fell 1.9 percent to 1,631.87.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX), the Russian oil producer,
headed for its biggest decline in more than a week, losing 2.1
percent to 126.66 rubles. Crude slid in  New York  on bets by
investors that fuel demand will fall because of faltering global
economic growth.  Bank Vozrozhdenie (VZRZ RX) rose for a second day after the
Russian regional lender said net income in the first half more
than tripled to 712 million rubles. The shares climbed as much
as 1.6 percent and last traded 0.5 percent higher at 925 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX),  Russia â€™s largest mining
company, headed for its lowest close in a week, losing 1.8
percent to 6,587 rubles. Copper dropped as estimates showed
inventories of the metal in  China  may have rebounded.  To contact the reporter on this story:
